= Background
<background>

Though the concept of data lakes has existed since the 2000s, the term was only coined in 2011 by James Dixon#cite(<ibm-what-datalake>).
Most of the current solutions are thus still in active development, and often in a pre-release.
This means that the documentation used might have been changed multiple times during writing.

In this section, we will discuss multiple approaches and technologies used within data lake systems.

